### Vegetarian Supreme Pizza

**Ingredients:**
- 1 pizza dough
- 1/2 cup tomato sauce
- 1 cup bell peppers, thinly sliced (assorted colors)
- 1 cup mushrooms, sliced
- 1/2 cup red onion, thinly sliced
- 1 cup black olives, sliced
- 1 1/2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese
- Fresh basil leaves for garnish
- Olive oil
- Salt and pepper to taste

**Instructions:**
1. Preheat your oven to 475°F (245°C).
2. Roll out the pizza dough on a floured surface to your desired thickness.
3. Place the rolled-out dough on a pizza stone or baking sheet.
4. Spread a layer of tomato sauce evenly over the dough.
5. Arrange the sliced bell peppers, mushrooms, red onion, and black olives on top of the sauce.
6. Sprinkle shredded mozzarella cheese over the vegetables.
7. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
8. Drizzle with olive oil for added flavor.
9. Bake in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes or until the crust is golden and the cheese is melted and bubbly.
10. Remove from the oven and garnish with fresh basil leaves.
11. Slice and enjoy your Vegetarian Supreme Pizza!
